The paper deals with the problem of enabling a drone to fly through a narrow gap using an end-to-end policy network, which involves reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on the control and planning aspects of the problem, which are typically addressed in the robotics subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically neural networks, which are commonly used in the subfields of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves control systems, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
